function.name: custom_ticker_for_global_ethereum_price_index_gex
function.description: This is the subfunction for tool "global_ethereum_price_index_gex", you can use this tool.The description of this function is: "This endpoint can be used to generate a custom index in a certain currency. The “inex” path parameter represents “include” or “exclude”, you can choose to generate an index removing specified exchanges, or only including the few that you require."

inex.description: include - if you want the ticker to be calculated using only the exchanges sent as query parameter; exclude - if you want the price to be calculated using all exchanges, but the ones sent as query parameter.

symbol.description: ETH<fiat> where <fiat> is valid ISO currency (ex. ETHUSD)

function.name: all_ticker_data_for_global_ethereum_price_index_gex
function.description: This is the subfunction for tool "global_ethereum_price_index_gex", you can use this tool.The description of this function is: "If no query parameters are sent, then returns ticker data for every supported symbol. If fiat(s) are sent as parameters, then only the ticker for those values is sent."

fiat.description: Comma separated list of ISO currency codes (ex. USD,EUR)

function.name: ticker_changes_for_global_ethereum_price_index_gex
function.description: This is the subfunction for tool "global_ethereum_price_index_gex", you can use this tool.The description of this function is: "Returns ticker values and price changes for specified market and symbol."

symbol.description: Possible values: ETH<fiat> where <fiat> is valid ISO currency (ex. ETHUSD)
